## Functions
A function declaration consists of the keyword func, the name of the function, a parameter list (empty for main), 
a result list (also empty here) and the body of the function.

func function_name ( [parameter-list] ) [result-list] {
    //body of the function
}

- Parameters: when invoking a function we pass a value to the parameters. A parameter is like a placeholder. They 
  are optional.
- Returns: A function can return a list of values, the return-types is the list of data types of the values that 
  the function returns.
  
